=== assistant text ===
The Raman spectrum from `graphene.dat` was parsed, where each line contained two $(x, y)$ pairs separated by a tab, and the comma served as a decimal separator. The $x$ values (Raman shift) were sorted to ensure a continuous spectrum. 

The G and 2D peaks were fitted using a Lorentzian model:
$$f(x) = \text{amplitude} \cdot \frac{\gamma^2}{(x - x_0)^2 + \gamma^2} + \text{offset}$$

The fitting was performed using `scipy.optimize.curve_fit` with physically motivated bounds to ensure stable convergence. The resulting parameters were saved to `/app/results.json`.

